    {
      "type": "reading",
      "sequence": 2,
      "audio_script": "Listen to John chapters 18 through 21. Jesus was arrested in the garden. When the soldiers came, Jesus said, 'I am he,' and they fell to the ground. Peter struck the servant, but Jesus said, 'Put your sword away. Shall I not drink the cup the Father has given me?' Jesus stood before Pilate and said, 'My kingdom is not of this world... For this purpose I have come into the world—to bear witness to the truth.' The crowd demanded crucifixion. Jesus was crucified at Golgotha. Pilate's inscription read, 'Jesus of Nazareth, the King of the Jews.' On the cross Jesus said, 'It is finished,' and gave up his spirit. His side was pierced, and blood and water came out. Joseph of Arimathea and Nicodemus buried Him in a new tomb. On the first day of the week, Mary Magdalene found the tomb empty. Jesus appeared to her and said, 'Mary.' She recognized Him and announced, 'I have seen the Lord.' Jesus appeared to the disciples and said, 'Peace be with you.' Thomas doubted until Jesus invited him to touch His wounds. Thomas confessed, 'My Lord and my God!' Jesus said, 'Blessed are those who have not seen and yet have believed.' Later at the Sea of Tiberias, Jesus provided a miraculous catch and breakfast. He restored Peter three times: 'Do you love me?... Feed my lambs... Tend my sheep... Feed my sheep... Follow me.'",
