      "sequence": 4,
      "audio_script": "Doctrine and character belong together. Leadership credibility is moral before managerial. The church is pillar and support of truth in the world.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "type": "themes",
      "sequence": 5,
      "audio_script": "Key themes include sound doctrine, grace for sinners, prayer, qualified leadership, and church order.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "sequence": 6,
      "audio_script": "Review question: What does Paul say is the pillar and foundation of truth in 1 Timothy 3:15? Answer: the church of the living God.",
      "correct_answer": "the church of the living God",
      "acceptable_variants": [
        "the household of god is the pillar and foundation of truth",
        "1 timothy 3:15 — the church as the support and ground of the truth",
        "the assembly of the living god upholds and guards the truth"
      ],
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "type": "close",
      "sequence": 7,
      "audio_script": "God's household must reflect God's truth. Next, Paul guides Timothy in pastoral endurance and practical care.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
