    },
    {
      "type": "analysis",
      "sequence": 4,
      "audio_script": "If Christ's sacrifice is complete, no further offering is needed. Confidence before God rests on Jesus, not repeated rituals. Perseverance flows from certainty in His finished work.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "type": "themes",
      "sequence": 5,
      "audio_script": "Key themes include better covenant, once-for-all sacrifice, cleansed conscience, assurance, perseverance, and warning against apostasy.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "sequence": 6,
      "audio_script": "Review question: What does Hebrews 9:22 say about forgiveness? Answer: without the shedding of blood there is no forgiveness of sins.",
