      "audio_script": "Christian suffering is not meaningless; it becomes witness when joined to Christlike gentleness and holy endurance. Leadership integrity strengthens whole-community resilience.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "type": "themes",
      "sequence": 5,
      "audio_script": "Key themes include apologetic hope, suffering for righteousness, shepherding, humility, vigilance, spiritual warfare, and grace.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "sequence": 6,
      "audio_script": "Review question: What does Peter say Christ's suffering left for believers in 1 Peter 2:21? Answer: an example, so that they should follow in his steps.",
      "correct_answer": "an example for believers to follow in his steps",
      "acceptable_variants": [
        "christ left an example of suffering for us to imitate",
        "1 peter 2:21 — his suffering was an example to follow",
        "he suffered leaving us a pattern to walk in his footsteps"
      ],
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "type": "close",
      "sequence": 7,
      "audio_script": "Stand firm in true grace under trial. Next, 2 Peter warns against false teachers and calls for holy readiness.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
  "metadata": {
    "difficulty": "intermediate",
    "testament": "new",
    "book": "1_peter",
